HEADWORD: Profectitious
<hw>Pro`fec*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>profectitius</ets>, fr. <ets>proficisci</ets> to set out,
proceed.]</ety> <def>Proceeding from, as from a parent; derived, as from
an ancestor.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The threefold distinction of <qex>profectitious</qex>,
adventitious, and professional was ascertained.</q>
<rj><qau>Gibbon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

